    "recap_headline": "Fresno State Athletics",
    "recap_text": "FRESNO, Calif.\n\u2013 Fresno State mounted a late rally but couldn't overcome an early deficit, falling 11\u20139 to CSUN on Tuesday night at Pete Beiden Field at Bob Bennett Stadium.\nThe Bulldogs dropped to 7-12 on the season, while the Matadors improved to 11-9.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nCSUN jumped out early, plating two runs in the first inning and adding another in the second to take a quick 3\u20130 lead. The Matadors continued to apply pressure in the third, extending the lead to 4\u20130 before Fresno State answered with a solo home run from\nCayden Munster\nto get on the board.\nAfter CSUN pushed the lead to 6\u20131 in the fifth behind a two-run homer from Vaughn Coleman, the Bulldogs responded. Fresno State scored twice in the fifth, highlighted by an RBI single from\nBrady Hewitt\nand a sacrifice fly from Michael Boyd to cut the deficit to 6\u20133.\nThe Bulldogs continued to chip away in the sixth inning. Munster delivered again with an RBI triple before\nEthan Payne\nfollowed with an RBI double, trimming the deficit to 6\u20135.\nHowever, CSUN answered with two runs in the seventh and then broke the game open in the ninth when Coleman launched his second home run of the night, a three-run shot that stretched the lead to 11\u20135.\nFresno State made things interesting in the bottom of the ninth, scoring four runs.\nSky Collins\ndelivered a two-run single,\nMarcus Nolen\nadded an RBI double, and Munster capped his big night with an RBI single to bring the Bulldogs within two. But the rally fell short as the tying run never came to the plate.\nNOTES\nFresno State out-hit CSUN 13\u201316 but left nine runners on base.\nThe Bulldogs scored six runs over the final four innings.\nCSUN's Vaughn Coleman accounted for more than half of his team's RBIs (6 of 11).\nFresno State turned two double plays defensively.\nUP NEXT\nThe Bulldogs are headed to St. George, Utah, for a duo of games against the Trailblazers, beginning on Thursday at 5:05 p.m. PT."
